==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: airborne
<hw>airborne</hw> <pos>adj.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>conveyed by or
through air, as dust or pollen; <as>as, a clean room is needed to avoid
<ex>airborne</ex> contaminants</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>WordNet 1.5</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>in flight; flying; -- said of an airplane.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Mil.)</fld> <def>carried directly to the site of
battle by aircraft; -- said of combat troops, <as>as, an
<ex>airborne</ex> division</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>PJC</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Air brake</ent>⟦br⟧
